CVE-2026-33186

# Go stdlib crypto/tls session resumption - affects: supabase CLI binary
# bundled in node_modules/supabase/bin/supabase (compiled with Go 1.25.5)
# Fix available in Go 1.25.7 but supabase npm package not yet rebuilt
CVE-2025-68121

# smallstep/certificates SCEP provisioner bypass — affects: caddy
# Only exploitable if Caddy's internal SCEP provisioner is enabled
# (we use Caddy only as a reverse proxy/ACME client, not as a CA)
# TODO: Remove when Caddy ships a build with smallstep/certificates >= v0.30.0
CVE-2026-30836

# libcrypto3 / libssl3 (Alpine 3.23.3 in node:20-alpine base) — affects: bloom-web
# OpenSSL heap overflow on 32-bit platforms during X.509 OCTET STRING hex
# conversion (input_len * 3 overflows for inputs > ~1.4 GiB). Bloom-web runs
# on x86_64 only, does not process untrusted X.509 certs, and does not print
# cert contents — none of the three exploit preconditions hold.
# Fix available in alpine libcrypto3 3.5.6-r0; pinned node:20-alpine SHA
# not yet rebuilt with it. Reassess on next node:20-alpine SHA bump.
# Upstream: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-31789
CVE-2026-31789
